<subSubSection pageId="8" pageNumber="9" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,399,1465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Diagnosis. The male genitalia of 
<taxonomicName box="[660,957,399,424]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Ptychocroca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineabasalis">
<emphasis box="[660,957,399,424]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ptychocroca lineabasalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
are most similar to those of 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Ptychocroca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="keelioides">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">P. keelioides</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the overall shape of valva. They can be distinguished from the latter by the absence of the subdistal keel of the aedeagus.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,399,1465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Description. Male forewing (
<figureCitation box="[652,737,519,545]" captionStart="FIGURES 28 – 35" captionStartId="29.[264,382,1703,1727]" captionTargetBox="[312,1274,334,1679]" captionTargetId="figure@29.[312,1274,326,1679]" captionTargetPageId="29" captionText="FIGURES 28 – 35. Adult males of Ptychocroca. 28, P. apenicillia; 29, P. nigropenicillia; 30, P. keelioides, 31, P. lineabasalis; 32, P. crocoptycha; 33, P. crocoptycha; 34, P. galenia; 35, P. s i m p l e x." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/168777/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number box="[707,737,519,545]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="31.0">31</number>
</figureCitation>
) without patch of upraised scales at base of costa. Male hindwing with hairpencil concealed in fold of vein CuP, with a patch of beige­orange scales on each side of vein adjacent to haripencil. Male genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[1032,1103,599,625]" captionStart="FIGURES 4 – 6" captionStartId="23.[264,382,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[323,1257,327,1669]" captionTargetId="figure@23.[313,1273,326,1670]" captionTargetPageId="23" captionText="FIGURES 4 – 6. Male genitalia of Ptychocroca; valvae spread, aedeagus removed (to left of capsule). 4, P. lineabasalis; 5, P. galenia; 6. P. g a l e n i a." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156576/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number box="[1087,1103,599,625]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="4.0">4</number>
</figureCitation>
) with uncus, socii, and gnathos as described for the genus. Transtilla with moderately small mesal fold. Valva broadest basally, venter nearly straight in basal 
<number box="[842,896,679,705]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="0.25">0.25</number>
, followed by short, distinct ventrocaudal convexity; disc of valva without comb; plicate area large. Aedeagus as described for genus, infrequently with dorso­median spines; vesica with cornuti forming a single row. Female genitalia (
<figureCitation box="[533,618,799,825]" captionStart="FIGURES 16 – 21" captionStartId="27.[264,382,1694,1718]" captionTargetBox="[333,1273,327,1657]" captionTargetId="figure@27.[313,1273,326,1670]" captionTargetPageId="27" captionText="FIGURES 16 – 21. Female genitalia of Ptychocroca and Haemateulia. 16, P. apenicillia; 17, P. nigropenicillia; 18, P. keelioides; 19, P. lineabasalis; 20, P. galenia; 21, P. crocoptycha;" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/156580/files/figure.png" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Fig. 
<number box="[588,618,799,825]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" value="19.0">19</number>
</figureCitation>
) with sterigma fairly long, bearing rounded sclerotized lobe at middle immediately posterad of ostium; a pair of slender, membranous, V­shaped pockets laterally; sclerite in colliculum situated laterally, adjacent to a second medially situated sclerite.
</paragraph>
