<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,399,1465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">
Distribution and biology. 
<taxonomicName box="[611,907,1279,1304]" class="Insecta" family="Tortricidae" genus="Ptychocroca" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Lepidoptera" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="lineabasalis">
<emphasis box="[611,907,1279,1304]" italics="true" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Ptychocroca lineabasalis</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is known only from Santiago Province, 
<collectingCountry box="[327,393,1319,1345]" name="Chile" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Chile</collectingCountry>
, from about 
<quantity box="[540,708,1319,1345]" metricMagnitude="2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="8.75" metricValueMax="12.5" metricValueMin="5.0" pageId="8" pageNumber="9" unit="m" value="875.0" valueMax="1250.0" valueMin="500.0">500 to 1250 m</quantity>
elevation. Adults have been collected from October through December. The early stages are unknown.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="8.[264,1323,399,1465]" pageId="8" pageNumber="9">Etymology. The specific epithet refers to the short linear portion of the ventral margin of the valva.</paragraph>
